article.description: Kawhi Leonard scored 18 points and San Diego State defeated TCU 68-51 Tuesday night.
article.headline: TCU falls as San Diego State shoots 61 percent from the field
article.linkText: TCU put away by hot-shooting San Diego State
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Kawhi Leonard scored 18 points and San Diego State defeated TCU 68-51 Tuesday night. The Aztecs (19-7, 8-4 Mountain West) shot 61 percent from the field in the game, and scored 48 of their points in the paint plus 11 free throws in 18 attempts. They only made one 3-pointer, by Leonard, in 10 team attempts. After the Horned Frogs (12-15, 4-8) led 6-4 on a Ronnie Moss jumper, San Diego State reeled off the next 13 points, led 29-19 at the break and kept a double-digit lead for nearly the entire second half. The final score matched the Aztecs' biggest lead of the night. Billy White had 17 points and nine rebounds for San Diego State. Moss led TCU with 15 points and Zvonko Buljan added 12. The Horned Frogs shot 40 percent from the field.
